msgctxt "mn121:5.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhu amanasikaritvā manussasaññaṃ, amanasikaritvā araññasaññaṃ, pathavīsaññaṃ paṭicca manasi karoti ekattaṃ. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant—ignoring the perception of people and the perception of wilderness—focuses on the oneness dependent on the perception of earth. "

msgctxt "mn121:5.2"
msgid "Tassa pathavīsaññāya cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati adhimuccati. "
msgstr "Their mind becomes eager, confident, settled, and decided in that perception of earth. "

msgctxt "mn121:5.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, āsabhacammaṃ saṅkusatena suvihataṃ vigatavalikaṃ; "
msgstr "As a bull’s hide is rid of folds when fully stretched out by a hundred pegs, "

#. VAR: pabbatavisamaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ → pabbatavisamaṃ sabbaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn121:5.4"
msgid "evameva kho, ānanda, bhikkhu yaṃ imissā pathaviyā ukkūlavikkūlaṃ nadīviduggaṃ khāṇukaṇṭakaṭṭhānaṃ pabbatavisamaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ amanasikaritvā pathavīsaññaṃ paṭicca manasi karoti ekattaṃ. "
msgstr "so too, ignoring the hilly terrain, inaccessible riverlands, stumps and thorns, and rugged mountains, they focus on the oneness dependent on the perception of earth. "

