msgctxt "mn121:11.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhu amanasikaritvā ākiñcaññāyatanasaññaṃ, amanasikaritvā nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasaññaṃ, animittaṃ cetosamādhiṃ paṭicca manasi karoti ekattaṃ. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant—ignoring the perception of the dimension of nothingness and the perception of the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception—focuses on the oneness dependent on the signless immersion of the heart. "

msgctxt "mn121:11.2"
msgid "Tassa animitte cetosamādhimhi cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati adhimuccati. "
msgstr "Their mind becomes eager, confident, settled, and decided in that signless immersion of the heart. "

msgctxt "mn121:11.3"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti: "
msgstr "They understand: "

msgctxt "mn121:11.4"
msgid "‘ayampi kho animitto cetosamādhi abhisaṅkhato abhisañcetayito’. "
msgstr "‘Even this signless immersion of the heart is produced by choices and intentions.’ "

msgctxt "mn121:11.5"
msgid "‘Yaṃ kho pana kiñci abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ tadaniccaṃ nirodhadhamman’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘But whatever is produced by choices and intentions is impermanent and liable to cessation.’ "

msgctxt "mn121:11.6"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati. "
msgstr "Knowing and seeing like this, their mind is freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance. "

msgctxt "mn121:11.7"
msgid "Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "When they’re freed, they know they’re freed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn121:11.8"
msgid "‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya12
msgctxt "mn121:12.1"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti: "
msgstr "They understand: "

msgctxt "mn121:12.2"
msgid "‘ye assu darathā kāmāsavaṃ paṭicca tedha na santi, ye assu darathā bhavāsavaṃ paṭicca tedha na santi, ye assu darathā avijjāsavaṃ paṭicca tedha na santi, atthi cevāyaṃ darathamattā yadidaṃ—"
msgstr "‘Here there is no stress due to the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, or ignorance. "

msgctxt "mn121:12.3"
msgid "imameva kāyaṃ paṭicca saḷāyatanikaṃ jīvitapaccayā’ti. "
msgstr "There is only this modicum of stress, namely that associated with the six sense fields dependent on this body and conditioned by life.’ "

msgctxt "mn121:12.4"
msgid "So ‘suññamidaṃ saññāgataṃ kāmāsavenā’ti pajānāti, ‘suññamidaṃ saññāgataṃ bhavāsavenā’ti pajānāti, ‘suññamidaṃ saññāgataṃ avijjāsavenā’ti pajānāti, ‘atthi cevidaṃ asuññataṃ yadidaṃ—"
msgstr "They understand: ‘This field of perception is empty of the perception of the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance. "

msgctxt "mn121:12.5"
msgid "imameva kāyaṃ paṭicca saḷāyatanikaṃ jīvitapaccayā’ti. "
msgstr "There is only this that is not emptiness, namely that associated with the six sense fields dependent on this body and conditioned by life.’ "

msgctxt "mn121:12.6"
msgid "Iti yañhi kho tattha na hoti tena taṃ suññaṃ samanupassati, yaṃ pana tattha avasiṭṭhaṃ hoti taṃ ‘santamidaṃ atthī’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "And so they regard it as empty of what is not there, but as to what remains they understand that it is present. "

msgctxt "mn121:12.7"
msgid "Evampissa esā, ānanda, yathābhuccā avipallatthā parisuddhā paramānuttarā suññatāvakkanti bhavati. "
msgstr "That’s how emptiness is born in them—genuine, undistorted, and pure. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya13, sc11
msgctxt "mn121:13.1"
msgid "Yepi hi keci, ānanda, atītamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā parisuddhaṃ paramānuttaraṃ suññataṃ upasampajja vihariṃsu, sabbe te imaṃyeva parisuddhaṃ paramānuttaraṃ suññataṃ upasampajja vihariṃsu. "
msgstr "Whatever ascetics and brahmins enter and remain in the pure, ultimate, supreme emptiness—whether in the past, future, or present—all of them enter and remain in this same pure, ultimate, supreme emptiness. "

msgctxt "mn121:13.2"
msgid "Yepi hi keci, ānanda, anāgatamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā parisuddhaṃ paramānuttaraṃ suññataṃ upasampajja viharissanti, sabbe te imaṃyeva parisuddhaṃ paramānuttaraṃ suññataṃ upasampajja viharissanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn121:13.3"
msgid "Yepi hi keci, ānanda, etarahi samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā parisuddhaṃ paramānuttaraṃ suññataṃ upasampajja viharanti, sabbe te imaṃyeva parisuddhaṃ paramānuttaraṃ suññataṃ upasampajja viharanti. "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: viharissāmā’ti → viharissāmīti (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn121:13.4"
msgid "Tasmātiha, ānanda, ‘parisuddhaṃ paramānuttaraṃ suññataṃ upasampajja viharissāmā’ti—"
msgstr "So, Ānanda, you should train like this: ‘We will enter and remain in the pure, ultimate, supreme emptiness.’ "

#. VAR: vo → te (mr)
msgctxt "mn121:13.5"
msgid "evañhi vo, ānanda, sikkhitabban”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how you should train.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "mn121:13.6"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "mn121:13.7"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, Venerable Ānanda was happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn121:13.8"
msgid "Cūḷasuññatasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

